Ncrack
High-speed network authentication cracker

Password Attacks
Description
Ncrack is a high-speed network authentication cracking tool built by the Nmap team. It supports RDP, SSH, HTTP, SMB, FTP, and more protocols.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which ncrack
Install command:

sudo apt install ncrack
Basic Syntax
ncrack [options] <target>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
ncrack -p ssh 192.168.1.1 -U users.txt -P pass.txt

SSH brute force	Crack SSH	
ncrack -p rdp 192.168.1.1 -U users.txt -P pass.txt

RDP brute force	Crack Windows RDP	
ncrack -p ftp 192.168.1.1 -U users.txt -P pass.txt

FTP brute force	Crack FTP	
ncrack -iX nmap_output.xml

From Nmap output	Auto-target services	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Identify target services
2
Prepare credential lists
3
Run ncrack against target
4
Review discovered credentials
5
Document findings
Understanding the Output
Shows discovered credentials with service and host details.

Important Warnings
•
Only crack with authorization
•
Can cause account lockouts
•
Use timing options for stealth
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
